P=2
0 = \log{a} + b (0) 
\log{2} = \log{a} +b (40) 
\log{4} = \log{a} +b (100)
A = \left (\begin{array}&1 & 0 \\ 1 & 40\\1 & 100 \end{array}\right )
b = \left (\begin{array}&0\\ \log{2} \\ \log{4} \end{array}\right )
\left (\begin{array}&\log{a} \\ b \end{array}\right )= (A^T A)^{-1} A^T b
P(t) = 2^{(3/38)(1+t/4)}
P(140) = 2^{(3/38)(36)} \approx 7.17\, \text{billion}
